Mom, where's my cards?

183
00:16:19,058 --> 00:16:20,889
Where's my cards?

184
00:16:35,108 --> 00:16:36,439
Is my other deck in here?

185
00:16:36,609 --> 00:16:38,008
Did you eat?

186
00:16:38,178 --> 00:16:40,078
Dad's down there waiting already.

187
00:16:40,246 --> 00:16:42,111
There were cards in our bathroom.

188
00:16:42,282 --> 00:16:43,544
Yes, I had a waffle.

189
00:16:43,717 --> 00:16:46,585
Since we're out of waffles,
I don't see how that's possible.

190
00:16:46,754 --> 00:16:48,085
It's a miracle.

191
00:16:51,859 --> 00:16:53,383
Gloves?

192
00:17:00,201 --> 00:17:01,190
Henry!

193
00:17:05,973 --> 00:17:07,372
Come on.

194
00:17:09,377 --> 00:17:10,708
Get in.

195
00:17:12,981 --> 00:17:14,312
Got it?

196
00:17:20,155 --> 00:17:22,715
<i>So no one's even sure
exactly where they are...</i>

197
00:17:22,891 --> 00:17:26,054
...because there's no borders
or landmarks or anything.

198
00:17:26,228 --> 00:17:28,958
And the town?
It's not even a town really.

199
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:32,329
It just is this camp where all these people
have gathered to hide.

200
00:17:32,502 --> 00:17:33,491
Right.

201
00:17:33,669 --> 00:17:37,127
All these deserters and guys
that got cut off from their armies.

202
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:40,469
All these people that are hiding
in the woods, trying to stay alive.

203
00:17:40,643 --> 00:17:42,543
This is where they all came.

204
00:17:42,712 --> 00:17:45,704
There's Thieves, Gray Mages,
Unbidden Warriors...

205
00:17:45,882 --> 00:17:47,907
...Dark Avians,
Riverwynders and Sappers.

206
00:17:48,084 --> 00:17:51,248
-There's, like, 15 different characters, okay?
-Okay.

207
00:17:51,722 --> 00:17:53,451
And nobody has any alliances.

208
00:17:53,624 --> 00:17:56,889
You can't even say who you are
because, you don't know...

209
00:17:57,060 --> 00:17:59,051
...maybe the person you're talking to...

210
00:17:59,229 --> 00:18:01,720
...maybe they're like your mortal enemy
in the wars.

211
00:18:01,899 --> 00:18:04,595
So it's just completely like
everybody for themselves.

212
00:18:04,768 --> 00:18:06,099
Sounds familiar.

213
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:09,205
It's really good.
I'm serious, you should really read it.

214
00:18:09,373 --> 00:18:12,536
Right. But by the time I finish it,
you'll be on to something else.

215
00:18:12,709 --> 00:18:15,474
-How much you wanna bet?
-I don't know. How much you got?

216
00:18:16,214 --> 00:18:18,478
-You got your bus pass?
-It's in my locker.

217
00:18:18,650 --> 00:18:21,517
You're not even gonna look at it,
are you?

218
00:18:21,686 --> 00:18:23,119
-The book?
-Yes.

219
00:18:23,288 --> 00:18:24,687
Bring it on Saturday, I'll....

220
00:18:24,856 --> 00:18:28,087
I did already. I left it in your kitchen.
It's got a red cover.

221
00:18:28,259 --> 00:18:29,385
Okay.

222
00:18:29,561 --> 00:18:31,961
Well, here we go.

223
00:18:32,130 --> 00:18:34,827
Go. Teach these people something,
would you?

224
00:18:38,938 --> 00:18:41,463
-See you later, Dad.
