01:19:11,097 --> 01:19:12,758
Good years.

1147
01:19:14,300 --> 01:19:18,464
And what I feel right now, if I'm honest?

1148
01:19:21,308 --> 01:19:23,799
I can't even say, it's so awful.

1149
01:19:24,945 --> 01:19:26,606
You can say it.

1150
01:19:29,149 --> 01:19:31,049
We caught a lucky break.

1151
01:19:34,054 --> 01:19:36,352
We did, didn't we?

1152
01:19:41,061 --> 01:19:44,498
Marty? We need to get up to the office.

1153
01:19:44,665 --> 01:19:46,394
-They accepted?
-In principle.

1154
01:19:46,567 --> 01:19:49,400
Don Jeffries wants us
on the phone in half an hour.

1155
01:19:49,570 --> 01:19:52,471
I tried to explain about Arthur,
but they're short on sympathy.

1156
01:19:52,640 --> 01:19:54,540
Wait a minute. U/North is settling?

1157
01:19:54,709 --> 01:19:58,770
They see a window. They wanna try.
It's their show. What are we gonna do?

1158
01:20:00,515 --> 01:20:03,644
You did what you could, Michael.
We all did.

1159
01:20:05,054 --> 01:20:06,385
It's....

1160
01:20:06,555 --> 01:20:08,216
It's what we got.

1161
01:20:09,358 --> 01:20:12,191
-You need a ride?
-No, thanks, I'm fine.

1162
01:20:44,994 --> 01:20:45,983
Hello.

1163
01:20:46,162 --> 01:20:48,757
Hello. Hi. I'm looking for Anna Kysersun.

1164
01:20:48,933 --> 01:20:50,025
<i>Who is this?</i>

1165
01:20:50,201 --> 01:20:53,693
Michael Clayton. I'm an attorney in
New York. I got your number from Arthur.

1166
01:20:53,871 --> 01:20:56,738
<i>-You have got some nerve.
-Excuse me?</i>

1167
01:20:56,907 --> 01:21:00,707
You get her all the way to New York City
and then leave her at the airport?

1168
01:21:01,112 --> 01:21:02,704
<i>This is not a complicated person.</i>

1169
01:21:02,880 --> 01:21:05,713
<i>This is a girl who's never been
farther than Milwaukee.</i>

1170
01:21:05,883 --> 01:21:07,874
<i>-Wait a minute. Now, wait.
-No, you wait.</i>

1171
01:21:08,052 --> 01:21:12,285
She's coming home tomorrow
and when she does, if you call here again--

1172
01:21:12,457 --> 01:21:14,755
Are you telling me she's
in New York right now?

1173
01:21:15,227 --> 01:21:17,218
<i>This is a young girl, do you hear me?</i>

1174
01:21:17,395 --> 01:21:19,829
She's in the city right now?

1175
01:21:19,998 --> 01:21:21,556
<i>What kind of people are you?</i>

1176
01:21:21,733 --> 01:21:24,759
Listen. You just stay on the phone
one second. One second.

1177
01:21:57,471 --> 01:21:58,699
<i>Anna.</i>

1178
01:22:01,108 --> 01:22:02,598
Anna?

1179
01:22:03,410 --> 01:22:06,379
My name's Michael Clayton.
I'm a friend of Arthur's.

1180
01:22:06,547 --> 01:22:09,209
I spoke with your sister.
She told me you were here.

1181
01:22:10,517 --> 01:22:12,382
Please open the door, Anna.

1182
01:22:23,698 --> 01:22:25,393
What are you thinking?

1183
01:22:26,201 --> 01:22:31,503
I don't know. I'll watch the door.
You check his car. Let's get some details.

1184
01:22:34,342 --> 01:22:37,608
He didn't want to say
exactly what it was.

1185
01:22:39,481 --> 01:22:43,315
Just that when I got here,
he would pick me up...

1186
01:22:43,485 --> 01:22:45,851
...and show me, and I would see...

1187
01:22:46,822 --> 01:22:49,689
...that it was something
that would win the whole case.

1188
01:22:52,895 --> 01:22:54,760
Even this morning...

1189
01:22:54,930 --> 01:22:56,522
...I mean, I thought:

1190
01:22:58,068 --> 01:23:02,732
"Okay, if I get to the airport
and the ticket's not there, then I'll know.

1191
01:23:02,906 --> 01:23:08,003
Okay, you're stupid,
and you can go home now."

1192
01:23:10,614 --> 01:23:15,449
But it was there and he paid,
like, 800 dollars...

1193
01:23:15,619 --> 01:23:18,281
...for a first-class ticket.

1194
01:23:18,455 --> 01:23:19,923
And I just....

1195
01:23:23,861 --> 01:23:25,795
I got on the plane.

1196
01:23:28,566 --> 01:23:30,500
I believed him.

1197
01:23:35,273 --> 01:23:39,937
You think maybe he was
in some way disappointed?

1198
01:23:40,778 --> 01:23:44,772
Let's say that he knew that you
told somebody else about all of this...

1199
01:23:44,950 --> 01:23:48,386
...and, I don't know, in some crazy way,
he was disappointed by that?

1200
01:23:49,488 --> 01:23:52,389
-But I didn't.
-You must have told somebody else.

1201
01:23:52,557 --> 01:23:54,115
No.

1202
01:23:55,294 --> 01:23:57,455
He made me promise.

1203
01:23:58,964 --> 01:24:03,333
You didn't tell anybody else about this?
Not one other person?

1204
01:24:04,470 --> 01:24:05,869
No.

1205
01:24:10,643 --> 01:24:13,578
He really was crazy, wasn't he?

1206
01:24:26,327 --> 01:24:29,194
-You talking about this?
-Let me see.

1207
01:24:30,698 --> 01:24:32,359
-You know what that is?
-Yeah.

1208
01:24:33,300 --> 01:24:36,360
You said a favor.
That's more than a favor.

1209
01:24:36,537 --> 01:24:38,698
Well, nobody's gonna know
where it came from.

1210
01:24:40,074 --> 01:24:42,508
-Are you that jammed up?
-What are you talking about?

1211
01:24:42,676 --> 01:24:45,304
Who asked for this?
It's the restaurant, right?

1212
01:24:45,479 --> 01:24:47,971
One of these guys you owe?
"Get me a seal."

1213
01:24:48,149 --> 01:24:49,776
You really wanna know?

1214
01:26:07,098 --> 01:26:09,328
This just gets better and better.

1215
01:26:10,968 --> 01:26:12,560
What are we doing?

1216
01:28:14,231 --> 01:28:15,255
Freeze!

1217
01:28:15,432 --> 01:28:18,162
Right there, asshole! Don't move!

1218
01:28:18,335 --> 01:28:20,599
-It's all right, I'm a friend!
-Get your hands up!

1219
01:28:20,771 --> 01:28:23,296
Get your hands up now! Now!

1220
01:28:23,473 --> 01:28:25,408
-What's in your hand?
-It's a book.

1221
01:28:25,577 --> 01:28:28,444
Drop it! Drop it, now! Drop it!

1222
01:28:28,613 --> 01:28:31,912
-Turn around. Slowly.
-All right. All right. Okay.

1223
01:28:32,083 --> 01:28:33,914
-Who else is here?
-Nobody.

1224
01:28:34,085 --> 01:28:36,519
-I said, who else is here?
-Nobody's here!

1225
01:28:36,688 --> 01:28:38,087
Check in there.

1226
01:28:38,890 --> 01:28:42,189
You move, I'll take your head off.

1227
01:29:12,058 --> 01:29:16,495
Now I owe this scumbag and his wife--
Who's a complete piece of shit in my unit.

1228
01:29:16,663 --> 01:29:18,756
-Now I owe them both my balls.
-I'm sorry.

1229
01:29:18,932 --> 01:29:20,923
-You know I am.
-"Nobody will know it's me."

1230
01:29:21,101 --> 01:29:24,161
You know what happens they don't
bury this, that I gave you this?

1231
01:29:24,337 --> 01:29:25,702
It's bad. I know it.

1232
01:29:25,872 --> 01:29:28,932
I'm 18 months away from my 20.
You just put my pension in jeopardy.

1233
01:29:29,109 --> 01:29:31,078
-You made your point.
-It's not a point!

1234
01:29:31,245 --> 01:29:33,611
-Who called 911?
-What?

1235
01:29:33,914 --> 01:29:36,849
The building was empty. I was quiet.
I wasn't there very long.

1236
01:29:37,018 --> 01:29:39,452
Who called it in?
Does that make sense to you--?

1237
01:29:39,620 --> 01:29:41,178
This never happened.

1238
01:29:42,490 --> 01:29:44,515
You got these cops thinking
you're a lawyer.

1239
01:29:44,692 --> 01:29:46,751
You got these lawyers thinking
you're a cop.

1240
01:29:46,927 --> 01:29:51,057
You got everybody fooled, don't you?
Everybody but you.

1241
01:29:51,232 --> 01:29:53,326
You know exactly what you are.

1242
01:30:06,948 --> 01:30:08,472
We tried calling you six times.

1243
01:30:08,650 --> 01:30:10,777
But your machine must be
busted or something.

1244
01:30:12,621 --> 01:30:14,111
We gave it our best shot.

1245
01:30:15,458 --> 01:30:17,949
We ran out of red covers.
We only had 2000 in stock...

1246
01:30:18,127 --> 01:30:19,992
...so we did the other thousand in blue.

1247
01:30:41,418 --> 01:30:42,908
Is everything all right?

1248
01:30:43,087 --> 01:30:44,315
It's fine, yeah.

1249
01:30:45,022 --> 01:30:48,082
You have a van or something?
Because I have 25 boxes back there--

1250
01:30:48,258 --> 01:30:51,318
Do me a favor. Hang on to them.

1251
01:30:51,495 --> 01:30:53,725
I'll come back and pick everything up
next week.

1252
01:30:53,897 --> 01:30:55,956
-Seriously? Thanks, man.
-Yeah.

1253
01:31:16,521 --> 01:31:17,886
Hello.

1254
01:31:22,962 --> 01:31:26,261
Don. You go ahead. I'll catch up to you.

1255
01:31:26,832 --> 01:31:28,129
What?

1256
01:31:35,541 --> 01:31:37,702
<i>Do you know Michael Clayton?</i>

1257
01:31:37,877 --> 01:31:39,367
<i>Yeah, why?</i>

1258
01:31:39,545 --> 01:31:41,308
We have a situation.

1259
01:32:01,101 --> 01:32:02,659
Hey, did they find you?

1260
01:32:02,836 --> 01:32:05,863
-Who?
-Marty. I don't think they've gone in yet.

1261
01:32:14,048 --> 01:32:15,379
Marty.

1262
01:32:15,716 --> 01:32:18,913
Your phone's off. There's too much
going on for your phone to be off.

1263
01:32:19,086 --> 01:32:21,077
-I need a minute.
-Yeah, well, we're late--

1264
01:32:21,255 --> 01:32:22,882
We never got to finish last night.

1265
01:32:23,057 --> 01:32:25,184
Did you close the place?
You look like hell.

1266
01:32:25,359 --> 01:32:28,420
-No, I left right after you left.
-If you say so.

1267
01:32:28,597 --> 01:32:31,293
We've been here all night.
We had to make an announcement.

1268
01:32:31,466 --> 01:32:34,731
Jean! I need the thing, the envelope.

1269
01:32:34,903 --> 01:32:38,100
I wanted your input. I couldn't get you.
I had to pull the trigger.

1270
01:32:38,273 --> 01:32:41,208
I put Bob Nast and Kim,
probably a mistake.

1271
01:32:41,376 --> 01:32:44,709
They're gonna pull together a memorial
service by the end of the week.

1272
01:32:44,880 --> 01:32:47,144
I told them to call you
if they need any help.

1273
01:32:47,650 --> 01:32:50,414
No, no, no.
The other one. The other one.

1274
01:32:50,987 --> 01:32:53,285
So we cut you a check this morning.

1275
01:32:53,456 --> 01:32:56,755
There's some strings attached.
And Barry....

1276
01:32:56,926 --> 01:33:01,056
There's no way around this,
Barry's gonna have to be involved.

1277
01:33:04,834 --> 01:33:07,268
What if Arthur was on to something?

1278
01:33:07,437 --> 01:33:09,098
What do you mean? On to what?

1279
01:33:09,273 --> 01:33:12,140
U/North. What if he wasn't crazy?
What if he was right?

1280
01:33:12,309 --> 01:33:14,470
Right about what?
That we're on the wrong side?

1281
01:33:14,645 --> 01:33:17,079
Wrong side, wrong way,
everything, all of it.

1282
01:33:17,248 --> 01:33:20,183
This is news?
This case reeked from day one.

1283
01:33:20,351 --> 01:33:22,342
I gotta tell you how we pay the rent?

1284
01:33:22,519 --> 01:33:25,249
What would they do?
What would they do if he went public?

1285
01:33:25,422 --> 01:33:28,823
What would they do? Are you fucking soft?
They're doing it.

1286
01:33:28,993 --> 01:33:31,428
We don't straighten the settlement out
in 24 hours...

1287
01:33:31,596 --> 01:33:33,655
...they're gonna withhold
$9 million in fees.

1288
01:33:33,832 --> 01:33:36,801
Then they'll pull out the video of
Arthur doing his flashdance.

1289
01:33:36,968 --> 01:33:38,697
They'll sue us for legal malpractice.

1290
01:33:38,870 --> 01:33:42,533
Except there won't be anything to win
because the London merger will be dead...

1291
01:33:42,707 --> 01:33:45,369
...and we'll be selling off
the goddamn furniture.

1292
01:33:45,844 --> 01:33:47,539
That's 80.

1293
01:33:48,046 --> 01:33:49,843
We're calling it a bonus.

1294
01:33:50,682 --> 01:33:52,707
Three-year contract
at your current numbers.

1295
01:33:52,885 --> 01:33:54,512
That's assuming this all works out.

1296
01:33:54,687 --> 01:33:55,847
You're doing this now?

1297
01:33:57,523 --> 01:34:00,856
Look, I agreed to this, okay?
But there's rules now.

1298
01:34:01,027 --> 01:34:03,894
You want the contract,
you sign a confidentiality agreement.

1299
01:34:04,063 --> 01:34:06,156
It's gonna be bulletproof
and retroactive.

1300
01:34:06,332 --> 01:34:08,061
Because Marty's too nice to say it...

1301
01:34:08,234 --> 01:34:12,034
...but with all you know about this place,
the clients and people who work here...

1302
01:34:12,204 --> 01:34:14,765
...it makes it a little weird
when you ask for 80 grand.

1303
01:34:15,442 --> 01:34:18,138
If I was gonna shake anybody down,
I'd come to you...

1304
01:34:18,312 --> 01:34:20,974
...and it wouldn't be for 80 grand.
Is this him or you?

1305
01:34:21,148 --> 01:34:23,742
-If I'm wrong, I apologize.
-You're way the fuck wrong.

1306
01:34:23,917 --> 01:34:25,145
So there you go.

1307
01:34:25,319 --> 01:34:26,980
Enough. Okay? Everybody.

1308
01:34:27,854 --> 01:34:30,015
He's an asshole, but he knows it.

1309
01:34:30,424 --> 01:34:33,689
And you're on the record.
Okay? Everybody happy?

1310
01:34:34,328 --> 01:34:37,025
-Don Jeffries is here.
-We're on the way.

1311
01:34:37,832 --> 01:34:41,928
Call Bob Nast.
Just see if they need help with this thing.

1312
01:34:45,506 --> 01:34:46,871
You're welcome.

1313
01:35:39,763 --> 01:35:42,130
You said 12. This is 75.

1314
01:35:42,299 --> 01:35:44,460
Well, don't get too excited.
You want a drink?

1315
01:35:44,635 --> 01:35:46,500
No. I'm working.

1316
01:35:48,939 --> 01:35:52,466
So we're square, then. No bad blood.

1317
01:35:52,643 --> 01:35:54,338
You're just doing your job.

1318
01:35:54,512 --> 01:35:55,979
That's right.

1319
01:35:56,914 --> 01:35:58,643
Take it easy, Gabe.

1320
01:35:59,650 --> 01:36:01,015
Michael.

1321
01:36:12,764 --> 01:36:14,197
<i>Check.</i>

1322
01:36:16,034 --> 01:36:17,296
<i>Check.</i>

1323
01:36:17,636 --> 01:36:20,366
-Check.
-Half the pot. Two hundred.

1324
01:36:20,539 --> 01:36:21,836
Two hundred to go.

1325
01:36:59,213 --> 01:37:00,976
So, what happened with the bar?

1326
01:37:01,148 --> 01:37:03,173
You just had to be a rock star, huh?

1327
01:37:25,673 --> 01:37:28,437
What are you doing? You just got here.

1328
01:37:28,610 --> 01:37:30,544
Guy plays nine hands, walks away.

1329
01:37:30,712 --> 01:37:34,877
I scare you away? What did I do?
Did I scare you away?

1330
01:38:10,654 --> 01:38:11,712
Get out.

1331
01:38:13,089 --> 01:38:15,217
<i>Get out of the car now.</i>

1332
01:38:16,961 --> 01:38:17,950
<i>-Walter?
-Michael.</i>

1333
01:38:18,129 --> 01:38:20,324
<i>-Michael. Thank God you're there.
-Yeah.</i>

1334
01:38:24,735 --> 01:38:26,669
You have eight...

1335
01:38:27,572 --> 01:38:30,302
<i>...six, five...</i>

1336
01:38:30,474 --> 01:38:32,806
<i>...four, three....</i>

1337
01:38:32,977 --> 01:38:34,604
<i>Get out of the car.</i>

1338
01:38:38,050 --> 01:38:41,076
<i>-Tell him to stay off the phone.
-All right. But you're on it?</i>

1339
01:38:41,687 --> 01:38:43,120
Am I clean?

1340
01:38:43,288 --> 01:38:44,516
Just keep walking.

1341
01:38:44,690 --> 01:38:46,920
You copy. Am I clean?

1342
01:38:47,125 --> 01:38:50,117
Just keep moving.
He's walking to the car.

1343
01:38:50,662 --> 01:38:54,223
<i>--to let him know you're on the way.
I'll get back to you with the details.</i>

1344
01:38:54,399 --> 01:38:56,833
<i>-Just give me two minutes.
-I'll be in the car.</i>

1345
01:39:00,540 --> 01:39:03,976
<i>I didn't finish. It's in, but I don't know.</i>

1346
01:39:32,139 --> 01:39:35,700
It's loose. I got a pulse.
He's up there somewhere, but....

1347
01:39:37,478 --> 01:39:39,412
Let's find a way to boost the signal.

1348
01:39:46,988 --> 01:39:50,185
-I don't know what Walter promised you--
-A miracle worker!

1349
01:39:50,358 --> 01:39:53,589
That's Walter on the phone,
20 minutes ago. Direct quote, okay?

1350
01:39:53,762 --> 01:39:55,593
"I'm sending you a miracle worker."

1351
01:39:55,764 --> 01:39:57,425
-Well, he misspoke.
-About what?

1352
01:39:57,599 --> 01:40:01,126
About the fact that you're the firm's fixer?
Or that you're any good at it?

1353
01:40:06,909 --> 01:40:08,843
We're up. Just got a signal.

1354
01:40:32,703 --> 01:40:35,069
There's nothing back this way.
What's he doing?

1355
01:40:35,238 --> 01:40:36,432
Maybe he's lost.

1356
01:40:36,606 --> 01:40:38,403
-Wait a minute.
-That's him.

1357
01:40:41,745 --> 01:40:42,973
He was alone, right?

1358
01:40:43,146 --> 01:40:45,944
-Yeah, I think so.
-Call it, yes or no?

1359
01:40:48,386 --> 01:40:50,013
We gotta turn around.

1360
01:41:20,252 --> 01:41:21,879
Talk to me.

1361
01:41:22,054 --> 01:41:23,612
It's strobing.

1362
01:41:23,789 --> 01:41:26,189
No, we're good. I think we're good.
Just keep going.

1363
01:41:42,008 --> 01:41:43,600
No, he turned. Somehow he turned.

1364
01:41:43,777 --> 01:41:45,142
-Where?
-He took--

1365
01:41:45,645 --> 01:41:47,613
-He took a left.
-I don't have a left.

1366
01:41:57,591 --> 01:42:00,526
-East. He's southeast.
-What, so we missed it?

1367
01:42:00,694 --> 01:42:02,821
-Or the grid is wrong.
-Hang on.

1368
01:42:13,007 --> 01:42:15,704
-We gotta go back to one.
-One is what? Where's our one?

1369
01:42:15,911 --> 01:42:18,903
Half a mile straight ahead.
Just keep driving. Just go.

1370
01:42:25,787 --> 01:42:28,415
It says we're closing.
But that's west. It can't be west.

1371
01:42:28,590 --> 01:42:29,648
The signal or the grid?

1372
01:42:29,825 --> 01:42:32,555
-It's both. It just keeps dropping out.
-Goddamn it.

1373
01:43:23,781 --> 01:43:25,248
Give me the cell.

1374
01:43:27,785 --> 01:43:29,480
Our signal's good.

1375
01:45:07,389 --> 01:45:08,651
What?

1376
01:45:11,294 --> 01:45:12,989
Thanks, Mickey.

1377
01:45:13,162 --> 01:45:14,823
Just get me out of here.

1378
01:45:22,538 --> 01:45:26,269
I wanna get a meeting scheduled on this,
soon as we can. Thursday at the latest.

